```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>JSON List Editor</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 20px;
        }
        #jsonDisplay {
            margin-top: 20px;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            padding: 10px;
            max-width: 400px;
            white-space: pre-wrap; /* Preserve whitespace for JSON formatting */
            background-color: #f9f9f9;
        }
        input[type="text"] {
            margin-right: 5px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<h1>JSON List Editor</h1>
<h2>Application JSON</h2>
<input type="text" id="newItem" placeholder="Add new item" />
<button onclick="addItem()">Add Item</button>
<button onclick="updateJSON()">Update JSON</button>

<div id="jsonDisplay"></div>

<script>
    let jsonList = {
        "items": ["Item 1", "Item 2", "Item 3"]
    };

    function renderJSON() {
        const jsonDisplay = document.getElementById('jsonDisplay');
        jsonDisplay.textContent = JSON.stringify(jsonList, null, 2); // Pretty print JSON
    }

    function addItem() {
        const newItemInput = document.getElementById('newItem');
        const newItem = newItemInput.value.trim();
        if (newItem) {
            jsonList.items.push(newItem);
            newItemInput.value = '';
            renderJSON();
        }
    }

    function updateJSON() {
        // This function can be used to perform any updates or actions needed
        alert("JSON updated! Check the display.");
    }

    // Initial render
    renderJSON();
</script>

</body>
</html>
```

### Explanation:
- **JSON Structure**: The JSON object is initialized with a key `"items"` that contains an array of strings.
- **Display**: The JSON is displayed in a formatted way using `JSON.stringify` with indentation for readability.
- **Add Item**: You can add new items to the JSON array, and the display will update accordingly.
- **Update JSON Button**: A button is included to indicate that the JSON can be updated, though it currently just shows an alert.

