I understand now that you want the entire content to be in raw JSON format while still being embedded within an HTML file. Below is an HTML file that serves as a web app, displaying raw JSON data and allowing you to edit it. The JSON data is presented in a way that can be manipulated through the web interface.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Raw JSON Editor</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 20px;
        }
        #jsonDisplay {
            margin-top: 20px;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            padding: 10px;
            max-width: 400px;
            white-space: pre-wrap; /* Preserve whitespace for JSON formatting */
            background-color: #f9f9f9;
        }
        input[type="text"] {
            margin-right: 5px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<h1>Raw JSON Editor</h1>
<h2>Application JSON</h2>
<textarea id="jsonInput" rows="10" cols="50"></textarea><br>
<button onclick="updateJSON()">Update JSON</button>

<div id="jsonDisplay"></div>

<script>
    // Initial raw JSON data
    let jsonData = `{
        "items": ["Item 1", "Item 2", "Item 3"]
    }`;

    function renderJSON() {
        const jsonDisplay = document.getElementById('jsonDisplay');
        jsonDisplay.textContent = jsonData; // Display raw JSON
    }

    function updateJSON() {
        const jsonInput = document.getElementById('jsonInput').value;
        try {
            // Validate JSON
            JSON.parse(jsonInput);
            jsonData = jsonInput; // Update raw JSON
            renderJSON();
            alert("JSON updated successfully!");
        } catch (e) {
            alert("Invalid JSON format. Please correct it.");
        }
    }

    // Initial render
    document.getElementById('jsonInput').value = jsonData; // Set initial JSON in textarea
    renderJSON();
</script>

</body>
</html>
```

### Explanation:
- **Raw JSON**: The initial JSON data is stored as a string in the `jsonData` variable.
- **Text Area**: A `<textarea>` is provided for users to input or edit the raw JSON.
- **Update JSON**: When the "Update JSON" button is clicked, the input is validated. If valid, it updates the displayed JSON; if not, it alerts the user.
- **Display**: The raw JSON is displayed in a formatted manner using a `<div>`.

You can copy and paste this code into an HTML file and open it in a web browser to see the raw JSON editor in action.
